[1.070, "o", "Certainly! To reverse a linked list in Python, you can use an iterative approach to traverse the list and create a new list that contains all elements from the original list but in reversed order.\r\n\r\nHere's how you can do it:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nclass ListNode:\r\n    def __init__(self, value=0, next=None):\r\n        self.value = value\r\n        self.next = next\r\n\r\ndef reverse\r\n"]
[6.007, "o", "\r\n\u001b[2m# qwen-demo on the L4, qwen-west on the A100 — one endpoint, two regions, your HA posture too.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
